Orderly Collaboration

Working with other people

  • Where do you store your code?
  • Where do you store your data?
  • Where do you store your outputs?
  • How will things change over time?
  • Is it sensitive?

The setup

Here we ignore the git side for now and focus on sharing outputs

library(orderly)
orderly_init("workdir/part3")
## ✔ Created orderly root at '/home/runner/work/orderly-tutorial/orderly-tutorial/workdir/part3'
## Warning: Can't check if files are correctly gitignored
## ℹ Your outpack repo is in a subdirectory ''workdir/part3'' of your git repo
## ℹ To disable this check, set the option 'orderly_git_error_ignore' to TRUE by
##   running `options(orderly_git_error_ignore = TRUE)`

Thom Rawson has kindly set up a bunch of case data for us to use. He’s put it in an orderly root that we can use as an orderly location.

Adding a location

orderly_location_add_packit("thom", "https://packit.dide.ic.ac.uk/training")
  • Here we have used the packit location type; you must be in the mrc-ide GitHub organisation to use this
  • Locations are just another orderly root where you can find packets
  • We can arrange a “path” based location on the network drive if this does not work!

oh no

Using packets from elsewhere

Two options

  1. Pull the packet to make it local (orderly_location_pull)
  2. Tell orderly which locations to use

Running with location

The result

Include many dependencies

What if we wanted to pull in all regions?

orderly_new("analysis-all")
## Warning: Can't check if files are correctly gitignored
## ℹ Your outpack repo is in a subdirectory ''workdir/part3'' of your git repo
## ℹ To disable this check, set the option 'orderly_git_error_ignore' to TRUE by
##   running `options(orderly_git_error_ignore = TRUE)`
## ✔ Created 'src/analysis-all/analysis-all.R'

with code:

regions <- c("east_of_england", "london", "midlands",
             "north_east_and_yorkshire", "north_west", "south_east",
             "south_west")
orderly_artefact(files = sprintf("%s.png", regions),
                 description = "Plot of cases over time")

fs::dir_create("cases")
for (r in regions) {
  orderly_dependency("cases",
                     'latest(parameter:region == environment:r)',
                     c("cases/${r}.csv" = "cases.csv"))
}

d <- lapply(sprintf("cases/%s.csv", regions), read.csv)
names(d) <- regions

for (r in regions) {
  png(sprintf("%s.png", r))
  plot(Week_Cases ~ Week, d[[r]])
  dev.off()
}

More new bits

Loop over dependencies:

for (r in regions) {
  orderly_dependency("cases",
                     'latest(parameter:region == environment:r)',
                     c("cases/${r}.csv" = "cases.csv"))
}
  • parameter:region == environment:r - the packet where the parameter region matches r from our running environment
  • "cases/${r}.csv" - string interpolation on exit

Other features are available, e.g.

  • parameter:region == this:nhs_region - match packet with parameter region that matches our parmater nhs_region

Run this
